Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: What a diamond in the rough... Amazing, make sure you book because this place is going places, super service, excellent food and attitude attitude attitude..... Over 300 whiskeys to choose from and each one is better than the last. I really really really recommend you try and visit

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: Wonderful cocktails in a beautiful location. The whiskey sour is on point. The egg white foam was perfection. You can count on good service and well crafted drinks at this establishment. Highly recommend.

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: Great place for a whiskey cocktail and if you are hungry you have a choice of some nice small Asian style dishes, on Tuesday tacos. It's a place with a very international vibe so don't expect a lot of Dutch being spoken.

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: You would think that only having whisky would get boring after a while, but the staff at JD always finds new drinks for me to try that expand my understanding of what whisky can taste like. They have a great selection of craft beers on tap. The kitchen is amazing (even for me as a vegetarian). Try their spiked cider in winter. <3

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text:
Absolutely delicious cocktails and the best service I have had in Amsterdam!
We sat outside but the interior looks super cozy and cool for when winter comes! â€¦

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text:
Nice place for whiskys and cocktails also.

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: Walked in to ask a question about a whiskey and got the most pleasant experience lol. The staff member was so helpful, they even reached out to a WhatsApp group of the local barmen and so, just to help find the answer for me and the â€¦

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: A good nook in the Jordaan area. Wide selection of whiskey from around the world with craft brews from local breweries. You get what you pay for.

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: Widest selection of whiskey I've ever seen in one location. Try something new neat or on the rocks or explore their awesome cocktail menu. The food is fantastic also if you get hungry after tasting a few whiskeys. The owner and staff couldn't have been nicer!

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: Huge fan of this whisky bar. The menu is full of drinks that will become your favorites and the people working there are friendly and welcoming. â€¦

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: Back here after 2 or 3 years. This place used to be a hidden gem with great drinks and cocktails. Success and tourism must've gone to it's head. A cocktail is 16 euro's! Drink is 4 Sips ~70 ml. Disappointing to see over-tourism chip away at authenticity.

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: Sure, certain that things can be improved, but I'm a big supporter of the concept. â€¦

Review Text: Amazing atmosphere, food and service! Advice: talk to the bartender and tell him the type of whisky you like. He will make you discover another side of appreciation. ;)

Review Text: Extensive whiskey menu, pretty friendly bartenders who will engage and recommend you your next dram. Got pretty crowded and tight in the bar on a Friday night, to be expected. But good vibes even if you're alone for a drink.

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: Popped in for one and ended up staying for 3 hours in this lovely bar. The fabulous chesterfield settee in the window is the perfect spot to drink and wile away a few hours people watching. The owner was chatty, helpful and overall has created a great atmosphere. Will definitely be back if I'm ever in the 'Dam again.

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text:
Every whisky fan and/or alcohol enthusiast should visit this place.
A wide variety of whisky and great drinks. The staff are very nice and the whole place looks charming.

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: A great place to have Whiskey and Whiskey cocktails. Their collection of whiskey is incredible! Although a bit pricey, it's a great place to try new whiskey. The bartender has a good knack for suggestions.

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: Fantastic selection of whiskey to choose from. Have the staff help you out with a choice. You may be judged if you ask for ice with your whiskey, but they wont kick you out. Science has proven that ice is ok with whiskey, so do what you will. It IS a whiskey bar, so don't go in there asking for a gin and tonic.

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: Wide variety of whiskey as well as curiously curated food menu. Relaxing atmosphere with quality music. Highly recommended if you want to rewind. A little on the pricey side, but it is worth it.

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: The waitress was mean and rude when I asked her for a flavoured whisky, such as vanilla, honey, whatever. And she made me the most expensive drink with no flavour, pretty dull and charged too much. Won't go back, it's not that great.

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: I loved my visit, Felix the bar tender was very welcoming and very friendly, the bar itself is very well maintained and with extremely nice ambiance, the whisky collection is WoW and pricing is somehow okay ... For real a 5/5 without any compliments

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: Two guys with laid back caps were bartending in this up scale whiskey bar. I was disappointed that they didn't offer a pipette to put a few drops of water into the whiskey. We also had to wait a little too long to get served. But the whiskey itself tasted great!

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: The owner took care of us. Excellent service. I had an old fashioned which was excellent. Decent bar food as well... The turkey burger was flavorful and the sweet potatoes fries were delish!

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
Review Text: Very friendly staff! Wide selection of whisky. Try the local Netherlands ones, like Millstone Rye. Very good whisky for a fair price.

Name: J.D. William's Whisky Bar
